- use case responsibilities

Expected flow:
UI → Provider → UseCase → Repository → DataSource

---

# Clean Architecture Planning Rules

## Presentation Layer
Responsibilities:
- UI
- navigation
- local UI state
- interactions
- loading/error states

Forbidden:
- Firebase calls
- API calls
- business rules
- serialization logic

## Domain Layer
Responsibilities:
- entities
- business rules
- use cases
- repository contracts

Must remain:
- framework-independent
- transport-independent
- highly testable

## Data Layer
Responsibilities:
- repositories
- datasource integrations
- DTOs/models
- serialization
- Firebase/API communication

Forbidden:
- UI logic
- widget dependencies

---

# Riverpod Planning Rules

Define:
- provider ownership
- provider lifecycle
- invalidation strategy
- caching strategy
- async boundaries
- dependency injection flow

Prefer:
- feature-scoped providers
- predictable state transitions
- isolated async handling
- minimal rebuild scope

Avoid:
- global mutable state
- provider coupling
- circular dependencies
- oversized providers

---

# Firebase & Backend Planning

Analyze:
- Firestore collections
- query patterns
- indexes
- real-time listeners
- offline behavior
- synchronization strategy
- security rules impact

Validate:
- scalability of queries
- pagination needs
- transaction requirements
- cache strategy
- retry strategy
- timeout handling

REST migration readiness requires:
- repository abstraction
- datasource isolation
- centralized serialization
- transport-agnostic entities
- no Firebase outside data layer

---

